  <english_manuscript>There was a man in Hj&#xF8;rring, he was a merchant and an innkeeper and he was called Niels L&#xF8;t. His wife she was called Karen and a man in Astrup, the old Skytte-Kr&#xE6;n had accused her of being a witch. Then Niels L&#xF8;t summoned him, he had to prove that the woman was a witch and they went to court. Then there was a big black dog that followed Niels L&#xF8;t to the court. They questioned Skytte-Kr&#xE6;n hard if he could prove that she was a witch. Then he turns to this black dog and says, "Stand up, Karen, and answer that." Then she stood there buck-naked in the middle of the courtroom with them. The man took off his chenille which he had on over his jacket and put it over his wife.</english_manuscript>
  <danish_publication>Der var en mand i Hj&#xF6;rring, han var kj&#xF6;bmand og gj&#xE6;st-giver og hed Niels L&#xF8;t, hans kone hun hed Karen. S&#xE5; havde den gamle Skytte-Kr&#xE6;n i Astrup beskyldt hende for at v&#xE6;re en heks, og Niels L&#xF8;t st&#xE6;vner ham da, han skal bevise, hvad han havde sagt. De kom s&#xE5; i retten med hverandre. S&#xE5; var der en stor sort hund, der fulgte med Niels L&#xF8;t i retten. De sp&#xF6;rger Skytte-Kr&#xE6;n st&#xE6;rkt til, om han kan bevise, at hun er en heks. S&#xE5; vender han sig til denher hund og siger: "Stat op, Karen, og svar til det." Da stod hun splittern&#xF8;gen i retssalen ved dem. Manden sled sig af hans chenille, som han var i oven hans frakke, og hyt den oven over hans kone.</danish_publication>
  <english_publication>There was a man in Hj&#xF8;rring, he was a merchant and an innkeeper and he was called Niels L&#xF8;t and his wife, she was called Karen. Then the old Skytte-Kr&#xE6;n from Astrup had accused her of being a witch and Niels L&#xF8;t summons him then, he had to prove what he said. They went to court. Then there was a big black dog that followed Niels L&#xF8;t to the court. They ask Skytte-Kr&#xE6;n if he can prove that she&#x2019;s a witch. Then he turns to this black dog and says, &#x201C;Stand up, Karen, and answer that.&#x201D; Then she stood there buck-naked in the middle of the courtroom with them. The man took off his chenille which he had on over his jacket and put it over his wife.</english_publication>
